wn]]]]\n[[File:Gerald Ford presidential portrait (cropped).jpg|thumb|120px|[[Gerald Ford]]]]\n* [[December 1]] &ndash; [[Claude Jade]], French actress (b. [[1948]])\n* [[December 4]] &ndash; [[Ross A. McGinnis]], American soldier, posthumously awarded the Medal of Honor (b. [[1987]])\n* [[December 5]] &ndash; [[David Bronstein]], Soviet Union chess grandmaster (b. [[1924]])\n* [[December 6]] &ndash; [[Han Ahmedow]], 1st Prime Minister of Turkmenistan (b. [[1936]])\n* [[December 7]] &ndash; [[Jeane Kirkpatrick]], American political theorist and U.N. ambassador (b. [[1926]])\n* [[December 9]] &ndash; [[Georgia Gibbs]], American singer (b. [[1919]])\n* [[December 10]] &ndash; [[Augusto Pinochet]], 31st President of Chile (b. [[1915]])\n* [[December 12]]\n** [[Paul Arizin]], American basketball player (b. [[1928]])\n** [[Peter Boyle]], American actor (b. [[1935]])\n* [[December 13]] &ndash; [[Lamar Hunt]], American businessman (b. [[1932]])\n* [[December 14]]\n** [[Ahmet Erteg\u00fcn]], Turkish record executive (b. [[1923]])\n** [[Mike Evans (actor)|Mike Evans]], American actor (b. [[1949]])\n* [[December 15]] &ndash; [[Clay Regazzoni]], Swiss race car driver (b. [[1939]])\n* [[December 18]] &ndash; [[Joseph Barbera]], American animator (b. [[1911]])\n* [[December 19]] &ndash; [[Rog\u00e9rio Oliveira da Costa]], Brazilian-born football (soccer) striker (b. [[1976]])\n* [[December 21]] &ndash; [[Saparmurat Niyazov]], 1st President of Turkmenistan (b. [[1940]])\n* [[December 22]]\n** [[Elena Mukhina]], Soviet artistic gymnast (b. [[1960]])\n** [[Galina Ustvolskaya]], Russian composer (b. [[1919]])\n* [[December 25]] &ndash; [[James Brown]], American singer (b. [[1933]])\n* [[December 26]] &ndash; [[Gerald Ford]], American politician, 38th President of the United States (b. [[1913]])\n* [[December 30]] &ndash; [[Saddam Hussein]], 5th President of Iraq (b. [[1937]])\n\n==Nobel Prizes==\n[[File:Nobel medal.png|right|120px]]\n* [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Chemistry]] &ndash; [