ne Pitney]], American singer (b. [[1941]])\n* [[April 8]] &ndash; [[Gerard Reve]], Dutch author (b. [[1923]])\n* [[April 11]] &ndash; [[Proof (rapper)|Proof]], American rapper ([[D12]]) (b. [[1973]])\n* [[April 12]] &ndash; [[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]], Indian actor and singer (b. [[1929]])\n* [[April 16]] &ndash; [[Silvia Caos]], Cuban-Mexican actress (b. [[1933]])\n* [[April 21]] &ndash; [[Tel\u00ea Santana]], Brazilian footballer and coach (b. [[1931]])\n* [[April 23]] &ndash; [[Alida Valli]], Italian actress (b. [[1921]])\n* [[April 24]] &ndash; [[Brian Labone]], English footballer (b. [[1940]])\n* [[April 25]] &ndash; [[Jane Jacobs]], American-born Canadian writer and activist (b. [[1916]])\n* [[April 29]] &ndash; [[John Kenneth Galbraith]], Canadian economist (b. [[1908]])\n\n===May===\n{{Main|Deaths in May 2006}}\n[[File:Floyd Patterson 1962.jpg|thumb|120px|[[Floyd Patterson]]]]\n* [[May 3]] &ndash; [[Karel Appel]], Dutch painter (b. [[1921]])\n* [[May 6]] &ndash; [[Shigeru Kayano]], Japanese activist (b. [[1926]])\n* [[May 11]] &ndash; [[Floyd Patterson]], American boxer (b. [[1935]])\n* [[May 12]] &ndash; [[Hussein Maziq]], Prime Minister of Libya (b. [[1918]])\n* [[May 13]] &ndash; [[Jaroslav Pelikan]], American historian (b. [[1923]])\n* [[May 14]] &ndash; [[Robert Bruce Merrifield]], American biochemist and academic, Nobel Prize laureate (b. [[1921]])\n* [[May 22]] &ndash; [[Lee Jong-wook]], Korean Director-General of the World Health Organisation (b. [[1945]])\n* [[May 23]] &ndash; [[Lloyd Bentsen]], American politician (b. [[1921]])\n* [[May 25]] &ndash; [[Desmond Dekker]], Jamaican singer and songwriter (b. [[1941]])\n* [[May 26]] &ndash; [[\u00c9douard Michelin (born 1963)|\u00c9douard Michelin]], French businessman (b. [[1963]])\n* [[May 27]] &ndash; [[Paul Gleason]], American actor (b. [[1939]])\n* [[May 30]] &ndash; [[Shohei Imamura]], Japanese film director (b. [[1926]])\n* [[May 31]] &ndash; [[Raymond Davis Jr.]], American chemist and physicist