], American actor (b. [[1949]])\n* [[December 15]] &ndash; [[Clay Regazzoni]], Swiss race car driver (b. [[1939]])\n* [[December 18]] &ndash; [[Joseph Barbera]], American animator (b. [[1911]])\n* [[December 19]] &ndash; [[Rog\u00e9rio Oliveira da Costa]], Brazilian-born football (soccer) striker (b. [[1976]])\n* [[December 21]] &ndash; [[Saparmurat Niyazov]], 1st President of Turkmenistan (b. [[1940]])\n* [[December 22]]\n** [[Elena Mukhina]], Soviet artistic gymnast (b. [[1960]])\n** [[Galina Ustvolskaya]], Russian composer (b. [[1919]])\n* [[December 25]] &ndash; [[James Brown]], American singer (b. [[1933]])\n* [[December 26]] &ndash; [[Gerald Ford]], American politician, 38th President of the United States (b. [[1913]])\n* [[December 30]] &ndash; [[Saddam Hussein]], 5th President of Iraq (b. [[1937]])\n\n==Nobel Prizes==\n[[File:Nobel medal.png|right|120px]]\n* [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Chemistry]] &ndash; [[Roger D. Kornberg]].\n* [[Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences|Economics]] &ndash; [[Edmund Phelps]].\n* [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Literature]] &ndash; [[Orhan Pamuk]].\n* [[Nobel Peace Prize|Peace]] &ndash; [[Muhammad Yunus]] and the [[Grameen Bank]].\n* [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Physics]] &ndash; [[John C. Mather]], and [[George F. Smoot]].\n* [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Physiology or Medicine]] &ndash; [[Andrew Z. Fire]], and [[Craig C. Mello]].\n\n==New English words and terms==\n*''agender''\n*''bucket list''\n*''crowdfunding''\n*''crowdsourcing''\n*''Eris''\n*''hypermiling''\n*''mumblecore''\n*''sizzle reel''\n*''ski cross''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.merriam-webster.com/time-traveler/2006|title=Time Traveler by Merriam-Webster: Words from 2006|author=|date=|website=merriam-webster.com|accessdate=May 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2006}}\n[[Category:2006| ]]\n", "name_user": "Kku", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eNew English words and terms:lx", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/